Yes, and you should use the archive node to check for events. So instead of checking for tx status, check the event. You can put up to 100 Fields to one event, so there is plenty of space for id information

```typescript
const MINAURL = "https://proxy.berkeley.minaexplorer.com/graphql";
const ARCHIVEURL = "https://archive.berkeley.minaexplorer.com";
const network = Mina.Network({
      mina: MINAURL,
      archive: ARCHIVEURL,
    });
    Mina.setActiveInstance(network);
```

Thank you for your test, now it is clear why I frequently see tx.wait() waiting a long time for the transaction already included in the block.

